What is Linux?
Linux is an open-source operating system (OS), similar to Windows and macOS.
An operating system is software that manages a computer's hardware and provides
services for computer programs.


Why is Linux important to learn?

Linux is important for software developers because it's widely used in technology.
Learning different operating systems shows employers that you can solve business problems on any OS.
It exposes you to new ways of doing tasks,helping you choose the best one for you.
Some find Linux faster or easier to use, and it gives more control over the system. 
Testing and solving problems on different systems helps you understand how they work.
Skills you gain on Linux are transferable to many other job roles.
